Mistakes I Made While Solving
Mistake 1

Initially computed RightMax using a nested loop.

Result:

O(n²)
Mistake 2

Initially tried using an ArrayList instead of an array.

Since the size is fixed, an int[] is a better choice.

Mistake 3

Initially thought of storing multiple maximum values.

Later realized that only the running maximum is required.

Learning from This Problem
Recognize repeated computations in the brute-force approach.
Use precomputation to eliminate redundant work.
If information depends only on previously processed elements, maintain it using a running variable.
Prefix/Suffix patterns often lead to O(n) optimizations.
Always derive the optimal solution from the brute-force solution instead of memorizing it.
